data.name: Fantasy Dilemmas: Is Tom Brady still a No. 1 quarterback?

data.message:
Yes, and he will come at a discounted price. Plus he has an early bye week, so you needed a decent QB for early in the season as a back up anyway.

Instead of taking Rodgers or Luck early, take Brady in the mids, and Eli as a back up. Eli opens with games vs ATL, Was, and Dallas. Then you start with good match-ups and have a fantasy stud like Brady the rest of the way. And Eli isn't the worst fantasy back-up.

That little bitch cheater Brady can give you early-round value the last 8 weeks with a healthy Gronk, Lafell and Edelman. And your team should be stack at the skill positions since you went QB late.
